{"id":"1606.09346","submitter":"Xing Wang","authors":"Xing Wang and Cheng Zhang","title":"Sharp endpoint estimates for eigenfunctions restricted to submanifolds\n  of codimension 2","comments":"17 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.AP math.CA math.DG math.FA math.SP","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Burq-G\\'erard-Tzvetkov and Hu established $L^p$ estimates ($2\\le p\\le\n\\infty$) for the restriction of eigenfunctions to submanifolds. The estimates\nare sharp, except for the log loss at the endpoint $L^2$ estimates for\nsubmanifolds of codimension 2. It has long been believed that the log loss at\nthe endpoint can be removed in general, while the problem is still open. So\nthis paper is devoted to the study of sharp endpoint restriction estimates for\neigenfunctions in this case. Chen and Sogge removed the log loss for the\ngeodesics on 3-dimensional manifolds. In this paper, we generalize their result\nto higher dimensions and prove that the log loss can be removed for totally\ngeodesic submanifolds of codimension 2. Moreover, on 3-dimensional manifolds,\nwe can remove the log loss for curves with nonvanishing geodesic curvatures,\nand more general finite type curves. The problem in 3D is essentially related\nto Hilbert transforms along curves in the plane and a class of singular\noscillatory integrals studied by Phong-Stein, Ricci-Stein, Pan, Seeger,\nCarbery-P\\'erez.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 30 Jun 2016 05:08:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 18 Jun 2020 13:43:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-06-22"}
